<TITLE> Purbo Bangla leader lynched in Tangail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Tangail, June 8 (bdnews24.com)  Villagers have lynched an alleged leader of the banned Purbo Bangla Communist Party on the bank of the river Dhaleshwari, a police official said Friday. The incident occurred late Thursday in Shibpur village under Baghil union of Sadar upazila, Tangail Sadar sub-inspector Mosharaf Hossain told bdnews24.com. The man's name is Sona Mia, 32, son of Lal Mia of Kashinagar village of Hugra union. He is known to be the outlawed group's commander in the area, Hossain said. There were several cases against Mia of killing people and assaulting police. Sona Mia was sentenced to death in his absence by hanging by a court for murdering Salamat Ullah Majnu, chairman of Baghil Union Parishad, he said. Police took the body to the police station at 8 pm. bdnews24.c
